Answers to homework questions in Part7:

a.) To learn more about the ls program, you can run 'man ls' to see the manual page (man page) for the ls command.

b.) The -a flag for ls stands for all, and causes ls to not ignore entries starting with .

c.) Linux is used in embedded systems because it is typically lower power / lower resource than Windows or any other operating system, it is free as in monetarily and as well as freedom, and Linux on ARM is actually very well supported.

d.) I am using SSH over my local network to connect to my Pi.  I am copying files back and forth using scp on my Linux laptop.
